Mapping enables you to bind a set of Vim commands to a single key.

:map <F5> i{<Esc>ea}<Esc>

F5 is the trigger key causes the command to be executed.
i{ :insert mode type {
<Esc> : leave insert mode
e : move to the end of the word
a: append }
leave insert move

:map lists all the mappings.


:mkvimrc file
